obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34916)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34916&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Tolls ^1[(Army and`
  line `Air Force)] Act, 1901;`
  line
  line `^2[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^3***.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on the first day of April, 1901.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1942, s. 2, for "(Army)".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O. 1950 for sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `3. The words "except Part B States" omitted by Act 3 of 1951. s. 3 and the Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34917)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34917&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[2. Definitions.--In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "authorised followers" means persons other than officers, soldiers or airmen,`
  line `who are employed by, or are in the service of, the Forces or Corps concerned, or are in the service of`
  line `any officer, soldier or airman of such Forces or Corps;`
  line
  line `(b) "carriage" means a vehicle for carriage or haulage other than one specially constructed for use`
  line `on rails;`
  line
  line `(c) "ferry" includes every bridge and other thing which is a ferry within the meaning of any`
  line `enactment authorising the levy of tolls on ferries, but does not include any ferry or other thing which is`
  line `included in the definition of railway in section 3 of the Indian Railways Act, 1890 (9 of 1890) ;`
  line
  line `^2[(d) the expression "the regular forces" means "the regular Army" as defined in clause (xxi) of`
  line `section 3 of the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950), and includes the "Air Force" as defined in clause (iv) of`
  line `section 4 of the Air Force Act, 1950 (45 of 1950);`
  line
  line `(e) "horse" includes a mule and any beast of whatever description which is used for burden or`
  line `draught or for carrying persons;`
  line
  line `(f) the expression "Irregular Corps" means any force (other than ^3[the Regular Forces or[^4the`
  line `Territorial Army or the National Cadet Corps]) raised and maintained in India under the authority of`
  line `the Central Government, ^5*** or any other force which may be notified in this behalf by order`
  line `published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(g) the expression "Indian Reserve Forces" means the forces constituted by the Indian Reserve`
  line `Forces Act, 1888 (5 of 1888) and includes officers belonging to the Army in India Reserve of`
  line `Officers or to the ^6[Regular Reserve of Officers] and members of ^7*** the Indian Air Force`
  line `Volunteer Reserve when subject to military or air force law, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(h) "landing-place" includes a pier, wharf, quay jetty and a stage whether fixed or floating;`
  line
  line `(i) "public authority", means the Central Government ^8*** or a State Government or a local`
  line `authority; and, so far as regards tolls levied by a railway company under section 4 of the Indian`
  line `Guaranteed Railways Act, 1879 (42 and 43 Vict. C. 41), or section 51 of the Indian Railways Act,`
  line `1890 (9 of 1890), includes such a railway company; and`
  line
  line `(j) "tolls" includes duties, dues, rates, rents, fees and charges, but does not include customs`
  line `duties levied under the Indian Tariff Act, 1934 (32 of 1934), octroi duties or town duties on the`
  line `import of goods, or fares paid for the conveyance of passengers on a tramway.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1942, s. 3, for section 2.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the First Schedule, for clause (d).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A.O. 1950.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "the Auxiliary Force (India) or the Indian Territorial`
  line `Force".`
  line
  line `5. The words "or of the Crown Representative" omitted by the A. O. 1948.`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "Indian Regular Reserve of Officers"`
  line
  line `7. The words "the Royal Air Force Volunteer Reserve and" omitted by the A.O.1950.`
  line
  line `8. The words "or the Federal Railway Authority" omitted by the A.O.1948.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34918)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Exemptions from tolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34918&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The following persons and property, namely :--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) all officers, soldiers and airmen of--`
  line
  line `(i) ^2[the Regular Forces]`
  line
  line `(ii) any Irregular Corps. ^3***`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) all members of ^5[the Territorial Army or of the National Cadet Corps,] when on duty or`
  line `when proceeding to or returning from duty,`
  line
  line `(c) all officers, soldiers and airmen of the Indian Reserve Forces when proceeding from their`
  line `place of residence on being called out for service, training, or muster or when proceeding back to`
  line `their place of residence after such service, training or muster,`
  line
  line `(d) all authorised followers of--`
  line
  line `(i) ^2[the Regular Forces]`
  line
  line `^6[(ii) the Territorial Army or the National Cadet Corps,]`
  line
  line `(iii) any Irregular Corps. ^7***`
  line
  line `^8* * * * *`
  line
  line `(e) all members of the families of officers, soldiers, airmen or authorised followers of--`
  line
  line `(i) ^2[the Regular Forces] or`
  line
  line `(ii) any Irregular Corps,`
  line
  line `when accompanying anybody of troops, or any officer, soldier, airman or authorised follower thereof`
  line `on duty or on the march,`
  line
  line `(f) all prisoners under military or air force escort,`
  line
  line `(g) the carriages, horses, and baggage, and the persons (if any) employed in driving the`
  line `carriages or in carrying the baggage, of any persons exempted under any of the foregoing clauses,`
  line `when such carriages, horses, baggage, or persons accompanying the persons so exempted under`
  line `the circumstances mentioned in those clauses respectively]`
  line
  line `^9[(h)] all carriages and horses belonging to Government or employed ^10[in the Indian] military`
  line `^11[or air-force] service and all persons in charge of or accompanying the same, when conveying any`
  line `such persons as hereinbefore in this section mentioned or when conveying baggage or stores, or`
  line `when returning, unladen from conveying such persons, baggage or stores,`
  line
  line `^9[(i)] all carriages and horses, when moving under the orders of military ^11`
  line `[or air-force) authority`
  line `for the purpose of being employed ^10[in the Indian] military ^11[or air-force] service.`
  line
  line `^9[(j) all animals accompanying any body of troops which are intended to be slaughtered for`
  line `food or kept for any purpose connected with the provisioning of such troops, and`
  line
  line `^9[(k) all persons in charge of any carriage, horse or animal exempted under any of the foregoing`
  line `clauses when accompanying the same under the circumstances mentioned in those clauses`
  line respectively,
  line
  line `shall be exempted from payment of any tolls--`
  line
  line `(i) on embarking or disembarking, or on being shipped or landed, from or upon any landingplace, or`
  line
  line `(ii) in passing along or over any turnpike or other road or bridge, or`
  line
  line `(iii) on being carried by means of any ferry,`
  line
  line `otherwise demandable by virtue of any Act, Ordinance, Regulation, order or direction of any`
  line `legislature or other public authority in ^12India:]`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall exempt any boats, barges or other vessels employed in`
  line `conveying the said persons or property along any canal from payment of tolls in like manner as other`
  line `boats, barges and vessels.`
  line
  line `^13[Explanation.--The persons or property exempted under clauses (d), (e) (g) and (j) shall be`
  line `deemed to accompany the Forces, troops, persons or property concerned, when the move of the`
  line `former is the direct result of, or is connected with the move of the latter, irrespective of the interval of`
  line `space and time between the two moves.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 1942, s. 4, for clauses (a) to (h).`
  line `2. Subs. by the A.O.1950 for "His Majestys Regular Forces".`
  line `3. The word "or" in sub-clause (ii) omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order 1956.`
  line `4. Sub-clause (iii) omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order 1956.`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and "the Schedule, for the Auxiliary Force (India) or of the Indian`
  line `Territorial Force".`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 3 and the Schedule, ibid., for the former sub-clause (a).`
  line `7. The word "or" in sub-clause (iii) omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order 1956.`
  line `8 . Sub-clause (iv) omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order 1956.`
  line `9. Clauses (i), (j), (k) and (l) relettered (h), (i), (j) and (k) respectively by Act 14 of 1942. s. 4.`
  line `10. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "in His Majestys".`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 10 of 1927, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule, for "a Part A State or a Part C State".`
  line `13. Added by Act 14 of 1942, s. 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34919)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Tolls on vessels transporting troops and baggage, etc., of troops embarked or disembarked.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34919&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) No tolls shall be leviable by any local authority in respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vessel employed by ^3[the Central Government] solely for the transport of troops, or`
  line
  line `(b) the horses, baggage or other effects of any troops embarking or disembarking at any port, or`
  line
  line `(c) carriages belonging to Government or employed ^1`
  line `[in the Indian] military ^2[or airforce]`
  line `service embarking or disembarking at any port.`
  line
  line `(2) In respect of all such vessels or troops, their families, their horses, baggage, and their effects, or`
  line `any such carriages as aforesaid, the local authority concerned shall. in addition to its duties in the`
  line `embarking and disembarking of the same, perform and supply all such reasonable services and`
  line `accommodation as may, from time to time, be required by ^3[the Central Government], and shall`
  line `receive payment for all such services and accommodation on such terms and for such periods as may, from time to time, be determined by`
  line `the Central Government in consultation with such local`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "in His Majesty"s".`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 1927, s. 2 and the First Schedule.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "the Government".`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34920)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34920&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Any person who demands and receives any toll in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `section 3 or section 4 shall he punishable with fine which may extend to fifty rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34921)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34921&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any owner or lessee, or any Company, railway administration or local`
  line `authority claims compensation for any loss alleged to have been incurred Owing to the operation of`
  line `this Act, the claim shall he submitted to the ^1[Central Government].`
  line
  line `(2) On receiving any such claim, the ^1[Central Government] ^3*** shall pass such order thereon as`
  line `justice requires, and shall give all necessary directions for the purpose of ascertaining the fact of the`
  line `case and of assessing the compensation, if any, to be paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1937, for "L. G.".`
  line
  line `2. The words "subject to the control of the G. G. in C." omitted, ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34922)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Rules.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34922&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government ^1*** may make rules to carry out the purposes and objects`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the Central`
  line `Government ^2*** may make rules providing for the form of passes to be given to persons or bodies of`
  line `persons or in respect of property entitled to exemption from the payment of tolls under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules under this section is subject to the condition of the rules being made`
  line `after previous publication.`
  line
  line `(4) All rules made under this section shall be published in the Official Gazette ^3*** and, on such`
  line `publication, shall have effect as if enacted by this Act.`
  line
  line `^4[(5) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case`
  line `may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and the L.G. with the previous sanction of the G.G. in C.", omitted, ibid.,`
  line
  line `2. The words "or the L G. with the previous sanction of the G.G. in C.", omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `3. The words "or in the local Official Gazette" omitted, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w. e. f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34923)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title [Repealed.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372&sectionId=34923&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_28_38_00019_190102_1523339562372
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `[Repeals.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1914 (10 of 1914), s. 3 and the`
  line `Second Schedule.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
